# SEO Rules

## Purpose
Organic growth per `docs/SEO_STRATEGY.md`.

## Requirements
- Public property routes: `/buy/{city}/{slug}` and `/rent/{city}/{slug}`.
- SSR or ISR with revalidate 300s; on-demand revalidate on publish.
- Meta title, description, OG, Twitter cards, JSON-LD RealEstateListing.
- Sitemap.xml per tenant; robots.txt disallow admin routes.
- Canonical URLs HTTPS; noindex draft/sold BR-S03.
- Programmatic city/area pages only if listing threshold met BR-S01.
- Core Web Vitals: next/image with dimensions, priority LCP image.

## Restrictions
- No UUID in public URLs.
- No indexing thin pages with zero listings.
- No cloaking different content for bots.

## Best Practices
- generateMetadata() in Next.js for each public page type.
- Structured data validated with Google Rich Results test in CI optional.
- hreflang ready for future i18n.

## Anti-Patterns
- Client-only render for property detail (bad for SEO).
- Duplicate meta titles across all listings.

## Examples

```tsx
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const property = await getPublicProperty(params.slug);
  return {
    title: `${property.bhk}BHK ${property.category} in ${property.area} | ${property.orgName}`,
    openGraph: { images: [property.heroImage] },
  };
}
```
